6 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 54-23.3 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Supervision for presentence programs.
9 The department of corrections and rehabilitation has the authority to supervise a defendant
10 while the defendant is participating in a prosecution - led, or pretrial diversion program under
11 section 1 of this Act or rule 32.2 of the North Dakota Rules of Criminal Procedure, or any other
12 pretrial services program.
13 SECTION 4. A new section to chapter 54-23.3 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Prosecution-led diversion supervision pilot program - Report.
16 1. The department of corrections and rehabilitation shall establish a prosecution - led
17 diversion supervision program as a pilot project in three counties in the state during
18 the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027 .
19 2. Beginning July 1, 2025, the department shall collaborate with the department of health
20 and human services, North Dakota association of counties, county state's attorneys,
21 the commission on legal counsel for indigent defense, county and regional correctional
22 facilities, and public and private treatment providers to develop guidelines and
23 procedures for the administration of the prosecution - led diversion supervision
24 program.
25 3. The department of corrections and rehabilitation shall select three counties for a pilot
26 project and enter contracts with third-party providers in partnership with the pilo t
27 counties to provide supervision, including monitoring and connection to services.
28 4. The department of corrections and rehabilitation shall implement the program no later
29 than July 1, 2026 .
