4 SECTION 5. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - PRETRIAL SERVICE PROGRAMS.
5 During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying costs and
6 savings associated with pretrial service programs operating in the state and opportunities to
7 reinvest savings to improve re-entry outcomes. The study must include the effect of pretrial
8 services on admissions to county jail, detention facilities, medical costs of participants, rate of
9 failure to appear in court, rate of recidivism, and rate of participation in treatment programs. The
10 study must identify opportunities for counties, courts, and state agencies to invest cost-savings
11 associated with pretrial services in programs, treatment, and services that will further reduce
12 recidivism and promote public health. The legislative management shall report its findings and
13 recommendations, together with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to
14 the seventieth legislative assembly.
